    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-25T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="440"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">262.84A41/5–2552: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 440<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States High Commissioner for Germany (<persName
                            corresp="#p_MJJ1" type="from">McCloy</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d440fn1">Repeated to Tel Aviv, London, Paris, and The
                        Hague.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-25T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 25, 1952—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3059. From the Secretary. Secretary saw <persName corresp="#p_AK1"
                        >Adenauer</persName> this morning re Israeli and Jewish claims. Stressed
                    importance US attaches to having a settlement of this matter reached which is
                    satisfactory to both sides. Emphasized fact that it is primarily a moral issue.
                    Expressed disappointment at reports that Gers seemed to be hoping for US aid to
                    assist them in settling the claims and pointed out that Gers wld be evading
                    moral responsibility if they relied on such a solution. Made clear Gers cld
                    expect no aid from US for this purpose.</p>
                <p>Chancellor in reply noted that resignation of Boehm, chief Ger negotiator in
                    talks with Israeli and Jewish reps had been withdrawn and Boehm was now
                    discussing claims in Paris with <persName corresp="#p_GN1">Nahum
                        Goldmann</persName>, who is acting as rep for Israeli as well as Jewish
                    material claimants. Chancellor said he had heard these discussions are going
                    well.</p>
                <p>Secretary expressed satisfaction this report and said he hoped Gers wld make
                    every effort to reach prompt and satisfactory settlement.</p>
                <p>New subj: Suggested reply from Secretary to <persName corresp="#p_SM2"
                        >Sharett</persName>’s letter (Paris tel 894, May 23 to Bonn)<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d440fn2">Text contained in telegram 3060 from Bonn, <ref
                            target="#d439">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> will be telegraphed shortly for Dept approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McCloy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
